ion/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig07c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig07d.jpeg" height="1036" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig07d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig08a.jpeg" height="1800" width="713" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig08a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig08b.jpeg" height="1800" width="1686" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig08b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig08c.jpeg" height="960" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig08c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig09a.jpeg" height="1355" width="1800" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig09a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig09b.jpeg" height="1800" width="1000" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig09b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig09c.jpeg" height="959" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig09c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig10.jpeg" height="1114" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig10" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10</span> Drawing shows the role of angiogenesis in the progression of disease from DCIS to invasive carcinoma. The myoepithelial cells that line the mammary duct normally express high levels of active angiogenesis inhibitors into the stroma, forming a protective boundary against DCIS (red-shaded cells). Focal disruption of the myoepithelial layer may lead to a loss of estrogen receptor expression, loss of heterozygosity, and decreased expression of tumor suppressors within the malignant cells immediately overlying the breach (blue-shaded cells), with resultant invasion of the stroma. <i>bFGF</i> = basic fibroblast growth factor, <i>ER</i> = estrogen receptor, <i>ME</i> = myoepithelial, <i>TIMP-1</i> = tissue inhibitor of matrix metalloproteinase 1.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig10">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig11a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1595" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig11b.jpeg" height="1167" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig11c.jpeg" height="1004" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig11c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig12.jpeg" height="1280" width="1176" aria-labelledby="fig12" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12</span> Van Nuys group 2 DCIS in a 52-year-old woman. Axial MR image of the left breast shows a region of nonmasslike enhancement with clumped internal enhancement. The superimposed kinetic curve, derived from signal intensity measurements in a selected region (red circle) within the lesion, shows slow enhancement in the initial period and gradual washout in the delayed enhancement period.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig12">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig13.jpeg" height="1280" width="1196" aria-labelledby="fig13" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13</span> Van Nuys group 2 DCIS in a 61-year-old woman. Axial MR image of the right breast shows a region of nonmasslike enhancement with stippled internal enhancement. The superimposed kinetic curve, derived from measurements in a selected region (red circle) within the lesion, shows a gradual increase in signal intensity that persists from the initial period through the delayed period of enhancement.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.305095073&amp;id=fig13">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.305095073/asset/images/095073fig14a.jpeg" height="1800" width="1260" loading